@startuml mobile-mvvm-sequence
title Mobile Layer — MVVM Flow\n(Flutter StatefulWidget · Riverpod Generator · Dio)

' ── Participants ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
actor       User                                                  as U
boundary    "View\n(ConsumerStatefulWidget)"                      as View
control     "ViewModel\n(@riverpod AsyncNotifier)"                as VM
entity      "Repository\n(FoodStallRepository)"                   as Repo
collections "Remote Data Source\n(DatabaseService — Dio)"         as RDS
database    "REST API"                                            as API

' ── Colour hints (optional, ignored if renderer doesn't support skinparam) ───
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor      #2C7BE5
  LifeLineBorderColor #2C7BE5
  ParticipantBorderColor #2C7BE5
  ActorBorderColor #2C7BE5
  NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
  NoteBorderColor #F9A825
}

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 1 · Screen opens — initial load ==
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

U   ->  View : Open screen
activate View

note over View
  **initState()**
  • attaches ScrollController listeners
  • schedules first build via Riverpod
end note

View -> VM : ref.watch(provider)\n→ triggers AsyncNotifier.build()
activate VM

VM  ->  View : emit AsyncLoading
View -> U    : Show CircularProgressIndicator

VM  ->  Repo : getFoodStalls(lang) /\ngetNearbyFoodStalls(lat, lng, radius, lang)
activate Repo

Repo -> RDS  : dio.get(Endpoints.getAllStalls(lang))
activate RDS

RDS  -> API  : GET /stalls?lang=vi
activate API

' ── Success path ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
alt HTTP 200 OK

  API  --> RDS  : 200 JSON [ { id, name, lat, lng, … } ]
  deactivate API

  RDS  --> Repo : ApiResponse<dynamic>.success(data)
  deactivate RDS

  Repo --> VM   : List<FoodStallModel>
  deactivate Repo

  VM   ->  View : emit AsyncData(List<FoodStallModel>)
  View ->  U    : Render map + stall list

' ── Error / network failure path ─────────────────────────────────────────────
else DioException (timeout / 4xx / 5xx / no network)

  API  --> RDS  : error response / timeout
  deactivate API

  RDS  --> Repo : ApiResponse.error(message, statusCode)
  deactivate RDS

  note over Repo
    **Offline fallback:**
    load bundled JSON from assets
    (lib/core/offline/stall_json/<lang>.json)
  end note

  Repo --> VM   : List<FoodStallModel> (offline data)\nor rethrows Exception
  deactivate Repo

  alt offline data available
    VM  ->  View : emit AsyncData(offlineStalls)
    View -> U    : Render offline content
  else no data at all
    VM  ->  View : emit AsyncError(message)
    View -> U    : Show error message + Retry button
  end

end

deactivate VM

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 2 · Provider state changes → View rebuilds automatically ==
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

note over View, VM
  **Riverpod ref.watch() subscription**
  Every time the AsyncNotifier emits a new state
  (AsyncLoading / AsyncData / AsyncError), Flutter
  schedules a rebuild of all widgets that called
  ref.watch(provider). No manual setState() needed.
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 3 · User triggers a retry ==
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

U   ->  View : Tap "Retry" button
View -> VM   : ref.read(provider.notifier).refresh()
activate VM

VM  ->  View : emit AsyncLoading
View -> U    : Show CircularProgressIndicator

VM  ->  Repo : getFoodStalls(lang)
activate Repo
Repo -> RDS  : dio.get(endpoint)
activate RDS
RDS  -> API  : GET /stalls?lang=vi
activate API

alt HTTP 200 OK
  API  --> RDS  : 200 JSON
  deactivate API
  RDS  --> Repo : ApiResponse.success
  deactivate RDS
  Repo --> VM   : List<FoodStallModel>
  deactivate Repo
  VM   ->  View : emit AsyncData(stalls)
  View -> U    : Render updated content
else Still failing
  API  --> RDS  : error
  deactivate API
  RDS  --> Repo : ApiResponse.error
  deactivate RDS
  Repo --> VM   : throws / returns offline data
  deactivate Repo
  VM   ->  View : emit AsyncError(message)
  View -> U    : Show error message
end

deactivate VM
deactivate View

@enduml
